    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
  <p class="gem-c-lead-paragraph ">
    Guidance for Cabinet Office social media channels.
  </p>

      
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row ">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
        <div id="contents" class="app-c-contents-list-with-body">
    
        <div class="responsive-bottom-margin">
          
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>Cabinet Office social media accounts are run by teams within the department. The accounts are used to communicate Cabinet Office and wider government announcements.</p>

<p>Teams may highlight content from other accounts, for example by liking or retweeting (depending on the platform) but this does not constitute any kind of endorsement.</p>

<p>Teams may also decide to connect on networks or to follow other accounts. This also does not constitute an endorsement and requests will not influence actions.</p>

<p>Owing to their sheer volume, we regret we are unable to respond to all requests/messages we receive via social media.</p>

</div>
</div>

        </div>

  </div>
    </div>
